===Etymology===
From {{der|en|it|Sicilia}}, from {{der|en|la|Sicilia|}}, from {{der|en|grc|Σικελία|}}, from {{m|grc|Σίκελος||{{w|Sicel}}}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈsɪsɨli/}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-Sicily.wav|Audio (Southern England)}}

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-proper noun|Sicilies}} {{qualifier|see usage notes below}}

# The largest [[island]] in the [[Mediterranean Sea]], politically part of Italy and thus of Southern [[Europe]], but geographically also close to Africa, and separated from Tunisia and Libya by the [[Strait of Sicily]].
# {{place|en|autonomous region|c/Italian Republic}}, officially named [[Regione Siciliana]] (''Sicilian Region'').

====Usage notes====
* English proper nouns ending in ''y'' usually add an ''s'' to form their plural (as in ''[[Germany]]s'' and ''[[Mary]]s''). ''Sicily'' is an exception to this pattern, as in ''[[Kingdom of the Two Sicilies|Kingdom of the Two '''Sicilies''']]''. For more, see {{pedia|English plurals#Plurals of nouns in -y|English plurals § Plurals of nouns in -y}}

